<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small private plane crashed into a
mountain in the south, and all seven people on board, including a
1-year-old, were killed, police said Sunday.
   The two-engine Cessna 421 disappeared Saturday night on a flight
from Corsica to Heubach, just a few miles from where it crashed.
