<HEAD>Conservatives Regain Lead in Opinion Poll</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher's Conservative
Party has regained its lead in popularity over the opposition Labor
Party, according to a poll published Sunday.
   The Harris Poll, published by The Observer newspaper, indicates
42 percent of those questioned favor the Conservatives, compared
with 39 percent for Labor.
   Last month, the two main parties were even at 41 percent, and in
February Labor led the Tories by 42 to 41 percent. The last time
Labor was ahead before then was October 1986.
