<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Cancer     04-23 0122</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Cancer,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>Most Bangladeshi Cancer Victims Die Without Treatment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two thirds of more than 200,000
Bangladeshis who develop cancer each year fail to receive proper
treatment and eventually die of the disease, news reports and
officials said Sunday.
   ``Cancer is taking a heavy toll every year with little medical
treatment available for the victims,'' said Dr. Abdul Hye, head of
the Cancer Institute of Bangladesh.
   United News of Bangladesh news agency, quoting World Health
Organization officials in Dhaka, said the country now has more than
800,000 cancer victims. It said most were unaware of their illness.
   Bangladesh, which has a population of 110 million people, has
only four major hospitals with facilities for detecting and
treating cancer.
</TEXT>
