<HEAD>Explosion Breaks Windows at Norwegian Refugee Center</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion outside a Norwegian center for
asylum- seekers broke windows but did not injure the 49 refugees
housed there, reports said Sunday.
   The Norwegian news agency NTB said the refugees were evacuated
to a safer facility after explosives planted in a tree near the Red
Cross center detonated and sent splinters and pieces of wood
through the windows of the building.
   Witnesses told police they saw a man running from the scene
immediately after the explosion, which occured at 1 a.m.
   Police said there was no bomb threat or other warning and that
there had been no previous trouble at the center in Eidsvoll, near
Oslo. The incident is being investigated by local and national
police, the report said.
