<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--BoatPeople     04-23 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Boat People,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Vietnamese Refugee Boat With 44 On Board Towed To Malaysia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Malaysian trawler fishing boat
towed a Vietnamese boat carrying 44 refugees to shore Sunday after
the two vessels collided in the South China Sea.
   Police confirmed the incident but declined to give further
details, the national news agency Bernama reported from Kuantan,
where the boat docked.
   Kuantan is 120 miles east of Kuala Lumpur.
   The Vietnamese are being held in a refugee camp pending
selection for permanent residence in the United States and other
countries. Malaysia accepts boat people only for temporary stay.
   There are now about 17,000 Vietnamese refugees in Malaysia, down
from a peak of 76,500 in June 1979.
